# Blog Conventions

## MDX Frontmatter Schema

Every blog post **must** have all of these fields:

```yaml
---
title: "Post Title Here"
date: "2026-05-19"         # ISO 8601 date, newest first in listings
excerpt: "One-sentence description for listing cards and SEO meta."
tags: ["nextjs", "devops"] # lowercase, hyphenated, 2-5 tags
readTime: "8 min read"     # estimate
coverImage: "/images/blog/filename.jpg"  # placed in public/images/blog/
published: true            # false = draft (excluded from listing)
---
```

## File Naming
- Filename = URL slug: `my-post-title.mdx` → `/blog/my-post-title`
- Use lowercase, hyphen-separated (kebab-case)
- Place in `content/blog/`

## lib/blog.ts API
```ts
getAllPosts()              // Returns PostMeta[] sorted by date desc, published only
getPostBySlug(slug)       // Returns { meta: PostMeta, content: string }
getPostSlugs()            // Returns string[] for generateStaticParams()
```

## Rendering
- `app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx` renders MDX with `next-mdx-remote/rsc`
- Blog prose is styled with `@tailwindcss/typography` (`prose prose-invert` classes)
- Custom MDX components: `<Callout>`, `<CodeBlock>` (to be added in components/)

## Image Handling
- Cover images go in `public/images/blog/`
- Use `<img>` with explicit width/height and `alt` text (next/image optimization is disabled)

## Writing Style for Blog Posts
- Write from first-person perspective (it's Himanshu's blog)
- Start with a compelling hook — a metric, problem statement, or surprising insight
- Include code examples where relevant (MDX supports JSX)
- End with key takeaways or next steps section

## Testing Blog Pages
```tsx
vi.mock('next-mdx-remote/rsc', () => ({
  MDXRemote: ({ source }: { source: string }) => (
    <div data-testid="mdx-content">{source}</div>
  )
}))

vi.mock('@/lib/blog', () => ({
  getAllPosts: vi.fn(() => mockPosts),
  getPostBySlug: vi.fn(() => ({ meta: mockPost, content: '# Hello' })),
  getPostSlugs: vi.fn(() => ['test-post']),
}))
```
